India Equities Movers: Fineotex, Idea, Sudar, Tata Coffee

-- B y   A m e y a   K a r v e
-- 
2011-03-11T11:15:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/india-equities-movers-fineotex-idea-sudar-tata-coffee.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 3:30 p.m. close in Mumbai.    India ’s Bombay Stock Exchange’s Sensitive Index, or Sensex,
fell 153.89, or 0.8 percent, to 18,174.09, and lost 1.7 percent
this week.  Fineotex Chemical Ltd. (FTXC IN), a chemicals company,
soared 86 percent to 130 rupees in its trading debut. Investors
bid for 1.57 times the shares on offer in its initial public
offering last month, when Fineotex sold shares at 70 rupees
apiece.        Idea Cellular Ltd. (IDEA)   lost 2 percent to 60.65
rupees, the most since Feb. 24. The mobile phone company was
sent a notice by the government’s Department of
Telecommunications that its license for Punjab will be canceled
as it hasn’t fulfilled network requirements, the Business
Standard reported, citing an official it didn’t identify. Rajat
Mukarji, a spokesman, didn’t immediately respond to a call on
his mobile phone.  Sudar Garments Ltd. (SUDAR IN) jumped 47 percent to 113.1
rupees as the ready-made garments and apparel maker started
trading. Investors last month bid for 1.55 times of shares on
offer in its IPO, in which the stock sold at 77 rupees apiece.    Tata Coffee Ltd. (TCO)  ,  Asia ’s biggest publicly traded
grower of the bean, surged 10 percent to a record 853.3 rupees
since its listing in July 2000 and taking its advance this week
to 48 percent. Trading volume today was 19-fold more than all of
last week’s. The company is “reaping” the benefit of high
coffee prices, Managing Director Hameed Huq said.  Robusta coffee prices in  London  rose 2.2 percent this week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ameya Karve in Mumbai at  at
 akarve@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
